There's a devil of a coal shortage because of the late war.

36
00:04:40,899 --> 00:04:44,961
This affects Swedish industry rather seriously.

37
00:04:45,002 --> 00:04:46,704
Wood largely replaces coal for fuel.

38
00:04:46,723 --> 00:04:52,026
Here are piles and piles of it in the streets, stacked for winter use.

39
00:04:52,047 --> 00:04:58,612
Since the first year of the war, except for a few weeks each winter, Swedes haven't any hot water in their apartment houses.

40
00:05:00,939 --> 00:05:04,399
Most Swedes think that their standard of living is too low.

41
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:08,802
For example, most people have bicycles instead of automobiles.

42
00:05:09,442 --> 00:05:12,023
Here are masses of them in the streets.

43
00:05:12,062 --> 00:05:13,642
Makes one do some driving problem.

44
00:05:14,423 --> 00:05:15,843
But it's good exercise.

45
00:05:15,903 --> 00:05:17,504
Or am I rationalizing too?

46
00:05:18,764 --> 00:05:22,365
The Swedish government is committed to a program of full employment.

47
00:05:23,146 --> 00:05:24,726
And plenty of work is going on.

48
00:05:26,487 --> 00:05:28,627
But not enough, many Swedish experts think.

49
00:05:29,468 --> 00:05:33,971
De vill få upp produktiviteten och för att göra det ska de vända sig till Amerika för tekniska studier.

50
00:05:33,990 --> 00:05:34,990
Men de vill också hålla inflationen ner.

51
00:05:35,011 --> 00:05:40,074
Så de har hållit på med sina krigstidspriser och krigstidsrationeringar av mat, mutter, sugare, bröd och sopa.

52
00:05:40,113 --> 00:05:41,415
Och priserna har blivit ganska ständiga.

53
00:05:41,435 --> 00:05:43,055
Så kanske Amerika kan lära sig något i tillväxt.

54
00:05:54,261 --> 00:05:54,982
Nu är vi i Småland.

55
00:05:55,041 --> 00:05:58,744
En väldigt stor del av de svenskar som migrerade till Amerika kom originalt från Småland.

56
00:06:22,021 --> 00:06:25,122
Så det är som att det ska inte mig att det är som att ju ålder folks.

57
00:06:25,142 --> 00:06:30,184
Det är en ålder säng att det småländer kan väcka stångs av en grov.

58
00:06:30,244 --> 00:06:31,744
Och det var en part av det.

59
00:06:31,764 --> 00:06:34,124
Det är som att de just bara haft att du där.

60
00:06:34,725 --> 00:06:36,404
Det är för det har dragit country där.

61
00:06:36,444 --> 00:06:39,725
Det gröta av det smålande grås var Linnaeus.

62
00:06:40,105 --> 00:06:41,406
Det kan ju få flowers.

63
00:06:42,005 --> 00:06:42,685
Det är hans hals.

64
00:06:44,086 --> 00:06:46,466
Smålande is mighty old country.

65
00:06:46,487 --> 00:06:48,206
Lats av det vikings som stannar upp.

66
00:06:48,307 --> 00:06:50,608
Everywhere from the Black Sea till Greenland.

67
00:06:50,648 --> 00:06:51,148
Helt från där.

68
00:06:52,096 --> 00:06:54,737
Here's old Kalmar Castle, as beautiful now as it was in the 12th century.

69
00:06:54,817 --> 00:06:57,237
Inside those walls in 1397, all Scandinavia was united for a little while.

70
00:06:57,278 --> 00:06:59,619
And if we push out to sea, a bit to the east, we hit Visby on the island of Gotland.

71
00:06:59,639 --> 00:07:02,519
Visby, once queen of the Baltic, the richest town of the Hanseatic League.

72
00:07:02,540 --> 00:07:03,461
It coined its own money

73
00:07:22,375 --> 00:07:26,331
Med ett sådant märkta imorgon vad det är i mörkontollet.

74
00:07:26,451 --> 00:07:26,612
Vars.

75
00:07:59,211 --> 00:08:07,115
Down we go, Tyskona, the granary of Sweden, and the home of many great men, like, well, Edvard Persson.

76
00:08:07,975 --> 00:08:13,119
It's a fat country, I mean flowers and things grow there like all get out.

77
00:08:33,729 --> 00:08:34,970
That's also true of Holland.

78
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:39,432
Nothing to do with the Dutch Holland except that it sounds the same and sort of looks the same.

79
00:08:39,511 --> 00:08:41,573
It faces the sea and warm winds from the west lave it.

80
00:08:41,594 --> 00:08:42,433
Nice country for a cycle trip.

81
00:08:42,474 --> 00:08:43,894
That's Varberg, Holland's ancient fortress.

82
00:08:43,914 --> 00:08:45,196
Looks like a tough nut to crack, doesn't it?

83
00:08:45,216 --> 00:08:46,556
Now we're moving north, up the west coast.

84
00:08:46,576 --> 00:08:47,677
This is Gothenburg, Sweden's second city.

85
00:09:02,235 --> 00:09:07,860
Swedens största port framför väst och har starka kulturella och ekonomiska förhållanden med England och Amerika.

86
00:09:07,980 --> 00:09:09,341
Det är en tydlig, tydlig gammal stad.

87
00:09:09,402 --> 00:09:13,764
Och hans attitude mot Stockholm är ungefär som Fort Worths till Dallas eller Brooklyns till The Bronx.

88
00:09:13,804 --> 00:09:16,147
Gothenburgs harbor är en av de busigaste i världen.

89
00:09:16,187 --> 00:09:18,208
Utifrån den här porten flödar frukten av svensk industrin.

90
00:09:18,229 --> 00:09:21,591
Lokomotiven för att sätta Europas smärta transportsystem i motion igen.
